quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  47,29,Or do those with sickness in their hearts think that God will not ňĻbe able toňļ expose their malice
  47,30,"Had We willed, We could have truly shown them to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, and you would have certainly recognized them by their appearance. But you will surely recognize them by their tone of speech. And God ňĻfullyňļ knows your doings ňĻO peopleňļ"
  47,31,"We will certainly test you ňĻbelieversňļ until We prove those of you who ňĻtrulyňļ struggle ňĻin God‚Äôs causeňļ and remain steadfast, and reveal how you conduct yourselves"
  47,32,"Indeed, those who disbelieve, hinder ňĻothersňļ from the Way of God, and defy the Messenger after ňĻtrueňļ guidance has become clear to them; they will not harm God in the least, but He will render their deeds void"
  47,33,"O believers! Obey God and obey the Messenger, and do not let your deeds be in vain"
  47,34,"Surely those who disbelieve, hinder ňĻothersňļ from the Way of God, and then die as disbelievers; God will never forgive them"
  47,35,"So do not falter or cry for peace, for you will have the upper hand and God is with you. And He will never let your deeds go to waste"
  47,36,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement. But if you are faithful and mindful ňĻof Godňļ, He will grant you your ňĻfullňļ reward, and will not ask you ňĻto donate allňļ your wealth"
  47,37,"If He were to do so and pressure you, you would withhold and He would bring out your resentment"
  47,38,"Here you are, being invited to donate ňĻa littleňļ in the cause of God. Still some of you withhold. And whoever does so, it is only to their own loss. For God is the Self-Sufficient, whereas you stand in need ňĻof Himňļ. If you ňĻstillňļ turn away, He will replace you with another people. And they will not be like you"